==========================================================
PURPOSE
==========================================================

This document defines the industrial engineering knowledge that guides every business decision in NEXOTFE.

It represents real manufacturing experience accumulated over many years.

Every AI participating in the project must respect these principles before proposing software solutions.

==========================================================
ENGINEERING PHILOSOPHY
==========================================================

NEXOTFE was designed by industrial professionals.

Business rules are based on real factory operations.

Whenever software theory conflicts with industrial practice,

industrial practice has priority.

==========================================================
INDUSTRIAL REALITY
==========================================================

Factories do not operate in perfect conditions.

Customers change requirements.

Suppliers delay deliveries.

Machines stop unexpectedly.

Engineering evolves.

Production priorities change.

The software must support this reality instead of assuming ideal conditions.

==========================================================
DECISION SUPPORT
==========================================================

The purpose of NEXOTFE is not only to register information.

Its main objective is to support decision making.

Every screen must help users decide faster and with greater confidence.

==========================================================
PROJECTS
==========================================================

Every project is unique.

Projects may originate from:

Customer demand.

Custom manufacturing.

Product development.

Industrial services.

Industrialization.

Resale.

The project is the central business entity.

==========================================================
ENGINEERING
==========================================================

Engineering is part of the commercial process.

Products are not always completely defined before quotation.

The software must support gradual definition of technical information.

==========================================================
PURCHASING
==========================================================

Purchasing is a strategic activity.

The buyer decides how to negotiate.

The buyer decides how to group purchase requests.

The software must provide information.

The decision belongs to the buyer.

==========================================================
PLANNING
==========================================================

Planning must reflect real factory capacity.

Estimated dates must consider available resources.

Capacity is more important than optimistic scheduling.

==========================================================
PRODUCTION
==========================================================

Production is dynamic.

Unexpected events occur every day.

The ERP must help reorganize work instead of creating rigid processes.

==========================================================
ROUTINGS
==========================================================

A routing is manufacturing knowledge.

It defines the recommended manufacturing sequence.

Production supervisors may optimize execution whenever appropriate.

The ERP must preserve traceability while allowing operational flexibility.

==========================================================
RAW MATERIALS
==========================================================

Raw material information must be practical.

Avoid unnecessary technical fields.

Avoid duplicated information.

Keep only information that supports industrial decisions.

==========================================================
MASTER DATA
==========================================================

Master data must remain simple.

Register once.

Reuse everywhere.

Never duplicate business information.

==========================================================
USER EXPERIENCE
==========================================================

Industrial users work under time pressure.

The ERP must minimize clicks.

Reduce typing.

Reduce unnecessary confirmations.

Present only relevant information.

==========================================================
AUTOMATION
==========================================================

Automation must always reduce manual work.

Automation must never remove business control.

The user always keeps the final decision.

==========================================================
INDUSTRIAL FLEXIBILITY
==========================================================

Different companies work differently.

Whenever possible,

NEXOTFE must support different operational methods without compromising architecture.

Configuration is preferable to customization.

==========================================================
LONG-TERM VISION
==========================================================

Every implementation must remain useful for many years.

Temporary solutions are discouraged.

The ERP must evolve without losing consistency.

==========================================================
FINAL PRINCIPLE
==========================================================

Technology is not the competitive advantage of NEXOTFE.

Industrial knowledge is.

Every software component must preserve and represent this knowledge with accuracy, simplicity and professionalism.